    {
      "key": "f238865a-4984-4316-aad7-0dc718e6974d",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-desktop\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Transition:** Direct students to Lesson 10, Level 5 to complete the End of Lesson Survey.\n"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f238865a-4984-4316-aad7-0dc718e6974d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5fa6e9ac-7030-4b8b-bcd1-bab05e667248"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fdd50021-7288-40f9-adcf-5b6cb0c10ab2",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa-solid fa-bullseye-arrow\"></i> **Goal of this activity:** To encourage students to critically assess the extent to which AI-generated content is truthful or misleading.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain the instructions and expectations with students. \n- Prepare the classroom space for movement.\n\n- Designate one side of the room as \"Real or Truthful\" and the opposite side as \"Designed to Mislead.\"\n\n- Have students begin standing in the center of the room.\n\n- Explain which side of the room represents each end of the spectrum and review expectations for respectful participation.\n\n- Explain that students should return to the center after each example so they approach each one with fresh thinking.",
        "name": "The Reality Spectrum: How Real is AI-Generated Content?",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Print or post visible signs for each end of the spectrum to make positioning clear. For each new prompt, have students return to the middle before making their decision—this encourages fresh thinking and movement. If time allows, let students briefly discuss their positions with nearby peers before moving into the full-class discussion after the final prompt."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fdd50021-7288-40f9-adcf-5b6cb0c10ab2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3251a330-ea88-448e-b2fd-fb96a9a6ed5a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6c627042-2288-4f88-bfdb-d88d5aebc39d",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6c627042-2288-4f88-bfdb-d88d5aebc39d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3251a330-ea88-448e-b2fd-fb96a9a6ed5a"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bf28c22e-bb4e-4a7d-a23f-a036bf3287ac",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-check-square-o\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Read the example aloud, then direct students to move to the spot on the spectrum that matches their opinion.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Consider highlighting the example of the 2022 ‘Théâtre D’opéra Spatial’ art piece that was created by MidJourney and won first place in the Colorado State fair art competition."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bf28c22e-bb4e-4a7d-a23f-a036bf3287ac",
        "lesson_activity.key": "3251a330-ea88-448e-b2fd-fb96a9a6ed5a"
      }
    },
